CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1958, pg. A12 reads: "10th Anniversary - New York Gay, Janie King, and Pittsburgh Gay, Mary McEnheimer, cut the 10th anniversary cake which was a feature of the Gay Northeasterners' luncheon, held last Saturday in the Penn-Sheraton Hotel. Mrs. King installed the Pittsburgh chapter 10 years ago, and Mrs. McEnheimer was the founder. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Large group portrait of Gay Northeasterner members, gathered in the Terrace Room of the Penn Sheraton Hotel for luncheon meeting
